}}'''Hiroyuki Kajihara''' (born 28 September 1966 in [[Yamanashi]], [[Japan]]) is a former [[rugby union]] footballer who played for [[Japan national rugby union team|Japan]]. Playing at {{Flanker}}, Kajihara played 21 [[Test match (rugby union)|Tests]] for Japan between 1989 and 1997. He scored 19 points from his four [[try|tries]]. Kajihara played in both the [[1991 Rugby World Cup|1991]] and [[1995 Rugby World Cup|1995]] Rugby World Cups for Japan. He played three games in each World Cup including matches against [[Scotland national rugby union team|Scotland]], [[Ireland national rugby union team|Ireland]] and the [[All Blacks]].

